snippet.textDisplay:
“It’s the Jimmy G effect.” Lynch has put together a great team, brick by brick. But once we got the Belichick/Brady groomed, two time super bowl winner jimmy g, everything changed. People got hyped. He’s hyped. Great quarterback. Doesn’t get enough love. But he don’t care, he’ll continue to win cuz that’s all he knows. “It feels great, baby!”

He’s a great quarterback, I don’t care what anybody says. He elevates the play of all those around him. Once we got him from NE he was so dialed in it was crazy. I think being away from Belichick, he lost a lil focus, but luckily he has recovered and has been playing wonderfully. He does throw too many int’s in my opinion, but luckily, because of who he is, the defense is there to back him up and then when he comes back on the field his offense produces. “He keeps drives alive.”

How many times has he had a timely 3rd down throw or throw a dime in a crucial situation? Jimmy Polo is the real deal idgaf what anybody says! Go 9rs!!!!!!!

snippet.textDisplay:
Used to dislike Kyle Shanahan since before the Atlanta debacle. He dismissed his terrible play calling (in SB vs Pats) and left town. Never owned up to it.

BUT he is a reeeeeaaalll good offensive coach AND he learned his lesson. 42 runs, 8 passes. The important thing is he KEPT calling running plays, didn't try to inject "creative" pass plays.

All around 49ers are the best team. The only advantage the Chiefs have is Mahomes and as the Broncos found out vsSeahawks ONE player isn't enough.
Super Bowl
49ers 33
Chiefs 30
